items.title: Urban and Regional Planning Resources
items.content_text:
### Planning Data Specifications / Transportation

*   [OpenDrive](https://www.asam.net/standards/detail/opendrive/) - The data that is stored in an ASAM OpenDRIVE file describes the geometry of roads, lanes and objects, such as roadmarks on the road, as well as features along the roads, like signals.

items.title: Awesome Cpp
items.content_text:
### Miscellaneous

*   [casacore](https://code.google.com/p/casacore/) - A set of c++ core libraries derived from aips++. \[LGPL]
*   [CCTZ (⭐615)](https://github.com/google/cctz) - a C++ library for translating between absolute and civil times using the rules of a time zone.  \[Apache-2.0]
*   [cxx-prettyprint (⭐563)](https://github.com/louisdx/cxx-prettyprint) - A pretty printing library for C++ containers. \[Boost]
*   [FastFormat](http://www.fastformat.org) - Fast, Safe C++ Formatting inspired by log4j and Pantheios. \[Simplified BSD]
*   [gcc-poison (⭐192)](https://github.com/leafsr/gcc-poison) - A simple header file for developers to ban unsafe C/C++ functions from applications.
*   [libsigc++ (⭐411)](https://github.com/libsigcplusplus/libsigcplusplus) - A typesafe callback system for standard C++. \[LGPL] [website](https://libsigcplusplus.github.io/libsigcplusplus)
*   [pprint (⭐923)](https://github.com/p-ranav/pprint) - Pretty Printer for Modern C++. \[MIT]
*   [pspsdk (⭐990)](https://github.com/pspdev/pspsdk) - An open-source SDK for PSP homebrew development. \[BSD/GNU GPL3]
*   [QtVerbalExpressions (⭐65)](https://github.com/VerbalExpressions/QtVerbalExpressions) - This Qt lib is based off of the C++ VerbalExpressions library. \[MIT]
*   [stdman (⭐969)](https://github.com/jeaye/stdman) - A tool that parses archived HTML files from [cppreference](https://cppreference.com) and generates groff-formatted manual pages for Unix-based systems. \[MIT]
items.content_html:
Miscellaneous

  • casacore - A set of c++ core libraries derived from aips++. [LGPL]
  • CCTZ (⭐615) - a C++ library for translating between absolute and civil times using the rules of a time zone. [Apache-2.0]
  • cxx-prettyprint (⭐563) - A pretty printing library for C++ containers. [Boost]
  • FastFormat - Fast, Safe C++ Formatting inspired by log4j and Pantheios. [Simplified BSD]
  • gcc-poison (⭐192) - A simple header file for developers to ban unsafe C/C++ functions from applications.
  • libsigc++ (⭐411) - A typesafe callback system for standard C++. [LGPL] website
  • pprint (⭐923) - Pretty Printer for Modern C++. [MIT]
  • pspsdk (⭐990) - An open-source SDK for PSP homebrew development. [BSD/GNU GPL3]
  • QtVerbalExpressions (⭐65) - This Qt lib is based off of the C++ VerbalExpressions library. [MIT]
  • stdman (⭐969) - A tool that parses archived HTML files from cppreference and generates groff-formatted manual pages for Unix-based systems. [MIT]
